    label "articulo::19::Towards digital well-being: evaluation of a minimal interface for navigation"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "Towards digital well-being: evaluation of a minimal interface for navigation"
    indice "19"
    Year "2024"
    ISBN ""
    ISSN "2007-3615"
    Doi "10.36677/legado.v19i36.22945"
    URL "https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/85219564115?origin=resultslist"
    Area "ISBD"
    Abstract "Digital well-being refers to the minimization of health risks caused by excessive use of technology, such as stress and high cognitive load. The work described in this paper focuses on the development of a minimal interface for on-foot navigation, reducing this load and fostering autonomy, competence, and relatedness by means of the Self-Determination Theory. Through a pilot study and the ACTA questionnaire, user experience was evaluated in physical and virtual environments, showing positive results in competence and autonomy, though limited in connection, particularly in virtual settings. It is proposed that minimal interfaces can alleviate cognitive load and enhance digital well-being."
  ]
