    label "articulo::27::A Comparative Study of Numerical Laplace Inversion Methods for HeatTransfer in Fractured Reservoirs"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "A Comparative Study of Numerical Laplace Inversion Methods for HeatTransfer in Fractured Reservoirs"
    indice "27"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN "978-1-9590-2561-0"
    ISSN "0160-3663"
    Doi "10.4043/35519-ms"
    URL "https://doi.org/10.4043/35519-ms"
    Area "CC"
    Abstract "Some fractured geothermal systems present analytical solutions expressed in Laplace space, necessitatingthe application of numerical inversion algorithms for accurate translation to time domain. This paperconducts a comprehensive analysis of some inversion techniques applied to geothermal equations, aiming toenhance precision and efficiency in the inversion process. Selected algorithms, including Stehfest, Bran&#269;ik,Euler, and den Iseger undergo evaluation based on computational performance and accuracy in capturingthe dynamic behavior of fractured geothermal systems. The study systematically compares the performanceof these algorithms through testing against benchmark cases. Results reveal diverse levels of accuracy andefficiency, providing valuable insights into their applicability across different models. Furthermore, theresearch underscores the computational advantages of utilizing Laplace space solutions, recognizing theirpragmatic benefits in addressing the inherent complexity of geothermal analytical solutions in real domain."
  ]
