    label "articulo::36::C-Xool: ERA5 Atmospheric boundary conditions toolbox for ocean modelling with ROMS, Version 1"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "C-Xool: ERA5 Atmospheric boundary conditions toolbox for ocean modelling with ROMS, Version 1"
    indice "36"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN ""
    ISSN "2352-7110"
    Doi "10.1016/j.softx.2025.102343"
    URL "https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105015588435?origin=resultslist"
    Area "CC"
    Abstract "We introduce C-Xool, an open-source, Python-based command-line toolbox that streamlines the preparation of atmospheric forcing data for the Regional Ocean Modelling System (ROMS). Provided with a user-generated grid file, C-Xool automates the downloading and processing of ERA5 reanalysis data (the fifth-generation global climate and weather dataset from the European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts), eliminating the need for manual handling of NetCDF (Network Common Data Form) files, a format predominantly used for storing multidimensional scientific data in atmospheric science, oceanography, and climate research. Users can customise the workflow through command-line arguments, specifying which variables to process, the requested time period, and the temporal resolution of the output. By automating this process, C-Xool supports reproducible ocean modelling, reduces the likelihood of manual errors, and accelerates the setup of ROMS computations. In addition, an integrated plotting tool enables users to visually inspect the generated forcing files, ensuring the data is consistent and ready for use."
  ]
