    label "articulo::58::Physics-Informed Neural Networks for Higher-Order Nonlinear Schr&#246;dinger Equations: Soliton Dynamics in External Potentials"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "Physics-Informed Neural Networks for Higher-Order Nonlinear Schr&#246;dinger Equations: Soliton Dynamics in External Potentials"
    indice "58"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN ""
    ISSN "2227-7390"
    Doi "10.3390/math13111882"
    URL "https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105007771323?origin=resultslist"
    Area "CC"
    Abstract "This review summarizes the application of physics-informed neural networks (PINNs) for solving higher-order nonlinear partial differential equations belonging to the nonlinear Schr &#38; ouml;dinger equation (NLSE) hierarchy, including models with external potentials. We analyze recent studies in which PINNs have been employed to solve NLSE-type evolution equations up to the fifth order, demonstrating their ability to obtain oneand two-soliton solutions, as well as other solitary waves with high accuracy. To provide benchmark solutions for training PINNs, we employ analytical methods such as the nonisospectral generalization of the AKNS scheme of the inverse scattering transform and the auto-B &#38; auml;cklund transformation. Finally, we discuss recent advancements in PINN methodology, including improvements in network architecture and optimization techniques."
  ]
