    label "articulo::89::An Affordable Robotic Manipulation Platform with Flexible Gripper and Vision for AI-Driven Control"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "An Affordable Robotic Manipulation Platform with Flexible Gripper and Vision for AI-Driven Control"
    indice "89"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN "979-8-3503-5736-3"
    ISSN "2832-1537, 2832-1529"
    Doi "10.1109/chilecon66915.2025.11475973"
    URL "https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/stamp/stamp.jsp?arnumber=11475973"
    Area "IA"
    Abstract "This paper presents the design and implementation of a low-cost, vision-guided robotic system for automated object recognition and manipulation. The platform integrates a MyCobot 280 Pi robotic arm with a custom 3D-printed, stepper-actuated gripper featuring compliant TPU fingers. A fixed overhead camera provides real-time visual feedback, enabling HSV-based color segmentation and homographic transformation for accurate object localization within a 400 mm &#215; 400 mm workspace. Experimental results validate the system&#8217;s ability to reliably detect, grasp, and relocate colored objects. Designed for flexibility and extensibility, the prototype supports research in AI-enhanced robotics, including one-shot learning with large language models (LLMs), tactile sensing, and closed-loop control strategies. Potential application areas include educational robotics, lab automation, light manufacturing, and AI-driven manipulation research."
  ]
