    label "articulo::165::Preference Learning for Multi-Objective Reinforcement Learning by Means of Supervised Learning"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "Preference Learning for Multi-Objective Reinforcement Learning by Means of Supervised Learning"
    indice "165"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN "978-981-96-3537-5, 978-981-96-3538-2"
    ISSN "0302-9743"
    Doi "10.1007/978-981-96-3538-2"
    URL "http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/978-981-96-3538-2"
    Area "IA"
    Abstract "In this work, we explore the integration of Training an Agent Manually via Evaluative Reinforcement (TAMER) into multi-objective reinforcement learning (MORL) environments to address the challenge of inferring decision-makers' preferences. We tested our approach on academic problems from MO-Gymnasium with an artificial decision-maker. Our results show that the approach can learn preferences within reasonable interactions."
  ]
