    label "articulo::197::A Reasoning System for Graded Modal Logic"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "A Reasoning System for Graded Modal Logic"
    indice "197"
    Year "2024"
    ISBN "979-8-3315-3211-6, 979-8-3315-3212-3"
    ISSN ""
    Doi "10.1109/conisoft63288.2024.00037"
    URL "https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/stamp/stamp.jsp?arnumber=10795561"
    Area "TC"
    Abstract "In this paper, we propose a deduction system for the modal logic K with graded modalities, which is obtained by adding numerical constraints to the modal operators. Graded modalities can be seen as a generalization of traditional modal operators since they include numerical bounds in the modalities, thus enabling the formal treatment of more detailed expressions, such as &#8220;there are at least n+1 individuals satisfying a certain property&#8221;, where n is a natural number. This kind of properties commonly arise in contexts such as concurrent systems: &#8220;if at least 3 processors are free, then proceed to compute the next task&#8221;, or epistemic logic:&#8221;if more than 2 people know P, then P is known&#8221;. The system is based on the notion of tree-hypersequents. We show the system is correct, i.e. sound and complete."
  ]
