    label "articulo::227::On some congruences and exponential sums"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "On some congruences and exponential sums"
    indice "227"
    Year "2024"
    ISBN ""
    ISSN "1071-5797"
    Doi "10.1016/j.ffa.2024.102451"
    URL "https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/85196966805?origin=resultslist"
    Area "TC"
    Abstract "Let &#949; > 0 be a fixed small constant, Fp be the finite field of p elements for prime p. We consider additive and multiplicative problems in Fp that involve intervals and arbitrary sets. Representative examples of our results are as follows. Let M be an arbitrary subset of Fp. If #M > p1/3+&#949; and H &#8805; p2/3 or if #M > p3/5+&#949; and H &#8805; p3/5+&#949; then all, but O(p1&#8722;&#948;) elements of Fp can be represented in the form hm with h &#8712; [1, H] and m &#8712; M, where &#948; > 0 depends only on &#949;. Furthermore, let X be an arbitrary interval of length H and s be a fixed positive integer. If H > p17/35+&#949; and #M > p17/35+&#949;, then the number T6(&#955;) of solutions to a six-variable congruence with terms mi/x_i^s satisfies an asymptotic formula of order H6(#M)6/p with error O(p&#8722;&#948;)."
  ]
