    label "articulo::230::On the orthogonal Gr&#252;nbaum partition problem in dimension three"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "On the orthogonal Gr&#252;nbaum partition problem in dimension three"
    indice "230"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN ""
    ISSN "0925-7721"
    Doi "10.1016/j.comgeo.2024.102149"
    URL "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.comgeo.2024.102149"
    Area "TC"
    Abstract "Gr&#252;nbaum&#8217;s equipartition problem asked if for any measure &#956; on R^d there are always d hyperplanes which divide R^d into 2^d &#956;-equal parts. This problem is known to have a positive answer for d <= 3 and a negative one for d >= 5. A variant of this question is to require the hyperplanes to be mutually orthogonal. This variant is known to have a positive answer for d <= 2 and there is reason to expect it to have a negative answer for d >= 3. In this note we exhibit measures that prove this. Additionally, we describe an algorithm that checks if a set of 8n in R^3 can be split evenly by 3 mutually orthogonal planes. To our surprise, it seems the probability that a random set of 8 points chosen uniformly and independently in the unit cube does not admit such a partition is less than 0.001."
  ]
