    label "articulo::240::Recent Advances on Principles of Concurrent Data Structures"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "Recent Advances on Principles of Concurrent Data Structures"
    indice "240"
    Year "2024"
    ISBN ""
    ISSN "0001-0782"
    Doi "10.1145/3653290"
    URL "https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/85200489158?origin=resultslist"
    Area "TC"
    Abstract "The text discusses the research conducted by a group at the Institute-de Matematicas of the Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico on the principles of distributed computing, specifically focusing on concurrent data structures. The goal is to survey recent advances in this area. Concurrent data structures are important for exploiting parallelism in modern multicore architectures. The text also explores the concept of linearizability, which states that every operation in a concurrent implementation appears to take effect instantaneously at a unique point in time. However, linearizability has limitations, and the text introduces the concept of interval-linearizability as an extension that allows for the specification of truly concurrent data structures. The group has developed techniques to overcome the limitations of linearizability and has proposed relaxed variants of classic data structures. Proving linearizability remains a challenging task."
  ]
