  ]
  node [
    id 2466
    label "articulo::303::Evaluation of dose reduction methods in cone beam X-ray microtomography"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "Evaluation of dose reduction methods in cone beam X-ray microtomography"
    indice "303"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN ""
    ISSN "1551-7616"
    Doi "10.1063/5.0308909"
    URL "https://doi.org/10.1063/5.0308909"
    Area "SIAV"
    Abstract "In this work, noise reduction filters were evaluated for micro-CT studies obtained under low-dose conditions, reducing the X-ray tube current down to one quarter of the standard settings (1 mA). Noise correction was evaluated using filters in the projection and reconstruction domains, namely: the bilateral (BI), anisotropic diffusion (DA) and non-local means (NLM) filters. All of them performed well, with the NLM filter achieving the best results, maintained a high structural similarity index value, and reduced noise by up to 55%. Better results were obtained when correcting directly in the projection domain. NPS analysis showed that noise reduction is strongest in high spatial-frequency components."
  ]
