    label "articulo::347::PumaMedNet-CXR: An Explainable Generative Artificial Intelligence for the Analysis and Classification of Chest X-Ray Images"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "PumaMedNet-CXR: An Explainable Generative Artificial Intelligence for the Analysis and Classification of Chest X-Ray Images"
    indice "347"
    Year "2024"
    ISBN "978-3-031-47639-6"
    ISSN "0302-9743"
    Doi "10.1007/978-3-031-47640-2_18"
    URL "https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/85177436974?origin=resultslist"
    Area "SIAV"
    Abstract "In this paper, we introduce PumaMedNet-CXR, a generative AI designed for medical image classification, with a specific emphasis on Chest X-ray (CXR) images. The model effectively corrects common defects in CXR images, offers improved explainability, enabling a deeper understanding of its decision-making process. By analyzing its latent space, we can identify and mitigate biases, ensuring a more reliable and transparent model. Notably, PumaMedNet-CXR achieves comparable performance to larger pre-trained models through transfer learning, making it a promising tool for medical image analysis. The model&#8217;s highly efficient autoencoder-based architecture, along with its explainability and bias mitigation capabilities, contribute to its significant potential in advancing medical image understanding and analysis."
  ]
