  node [
    id 3176
    label "articulo::396::Protection Of Sensitive Personal Information Contained In Digital Files Held By Individuals With Homomorphic Encryption And AI Assistance"
    tipo "articulo"
    nombre "Protection Of Sensitive Personal Information Contained In Digital Files Held By Individuals With Homomorphic Encryption And AI Assistance"
    indice "396"
    Year "2025"
    ISBN "979-8-3315-3559-9"
    ISSN ""
    Doi "10.1109/icecet63943.2025.11472089"
    URL "https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/stamp/stamp.jsp?arnumber=11472089"
    Area "RS"
    Abstract "In today's digital landscape, the exchange of sensitive personal data via mobile devices is widespread, yet inadequate safeguards often expose users to risks such as identity theft and online harassment. This research introduces Kamplae, a system crafted in Python and deployed through a Flask-based REST API, employing homomorphic encryption and artificial intelligence to protect personal information embedded in digital images. Kamplae secures metadata and bitmap content in jpeg, jpg, and png formats, adhering to legal standards in Mexico and the European Union. The study reviews prior work on personal data protection and the challenges posed by deep fakes, emphasising the need for robust regulatory frameworks to counter digital violence. It explores various encryption methods&#8212;symmetric, asymmetric, and hybrid&#8212;alongside relevant legal provisions across regions. Kamplae aims to prevent image misuse and foster a secure, ethical digital environment. While promising, it highlights areas for enhancement, such as broader format support and user interface refinement, with limitations tied to specific format compatibility and mobile performance."
  ]
